2.00	Radical_environmentalist	Radical environmentalism	Whilst many people believe that the first significant radical environmentalist group was Greenpeace, which made use of direct action beginning in the 1970s to confront whaling ships and nuclear weapons testers, others within the movement, argues as Earth Liberation Front (ELF) prisoner Jeff "Free" Luers, suggests that the movement was established centuries ago. He often writes that the concept of "eco-defence" was born shortly after the existence of the human race, claiming it is only recently that within the modern development of human society, and individuals losing touch with the earth and its wild roots, that more radical tactics and political theories have emerged.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Earthfirstmonkeywrench.gif/180px-Earthfirstmonkeywrench.gif
